item.description:
@matzie wrote:

serversdownload:

yeh help me

You know oracle is a smart company looking to please commonwealth and idiots alike. they put a help screen in their commandline compilers for things like this.
typing “jar ?” in the command line, will give you a list of ways to jar a file. gives you the information you need.

Jarring a file is not a mopar-specific task/talent. You know that more than private servers and clients are written in java?(HOLY SHAT!) so more than one novice probably ran into this issue. Take to google. Instead of looking for “WHY IS IT ADDING THIS AND THIS” try asking “WHY IS IT NOT EXCLUDING THIS(these)” Perspective and common sense are your friend, don’t betray them.
